$ C++

Don't confuse c++ with the preprocessor whose executable name is → Linux/fhs/usr/bin/cpp[`cpp`].

The GNU → development/make[make] manual encourages to use the `.cc` suffix for C++ files.

→ development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/preprocessor

→ development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/CPP/classes-structs/

→ development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/CPP/keywords

{ Expressions

  Examples for expressions:
    • literal
    • variable
    • function call ?
    • …

  An expression has two properties
    • a type
    • a value category (such as prvalue, lvalue, xvalue)

}

